item.description: Status Flags Map: R744CHPA Based on: R744HCHF Flag fields This is a flag field with the following bit fields: Field Bit-Position Description r744hdeg 0 If set, channel path is operating at reduced capacity (degraded) or is not operating r744hsnd 1 If set, channel path is a sender path

item.title: Field - r744hcpi
item.description: Channel path identifier. Map: R744CHPA Based on: R744HCPI Description The range of values is x'00’ to x’FF'.

item.title: Field - r744hdeg
item.description: If set, channel path is operating at reduced capacity (degraded) or is not operating Map: R744CHPA Based on: r744hchf Post-Processed This virtual field corresponds to the flag at bit-position 0 of field r744hchf.

item.title: Field - r744hdev
item.description: If set, degraded flag is valid Map: R744CHPA Based on: r744hfl1 Post-Processed This virtual field corresponds to the flag at bit-position 3 of field r744hfl1.

item.title: Field - r744hfl1
item.description: Validity flag 1 Map: R744CHPA Based on: R744HFL1 Flag fields This is a flag field with the following bit fields: Field Bit-Position Description r744hhca 0 If set, coupling adapter ID and port number are valid r744hmov 1 If set, channel path operation mode is valid r744hlav 2 If set, latency is valid r744hdev 3 If set, degraded flag is valid

item.title: Field - r744hfl2
item.description: Validity flag 2 Map: R744CHPA Based on: R744HFL2 Flag fields This is a flag field with the following bit fields: Field Bit-Position Description r744hpcv 0 If set, Channel ID (CHID) is valid

item.title: Field - r744hfla
item.description: Validity bit mask. Map: R744CHPA Based on: R744HFLA Description Each bit position represents the validity of a channel path attribute

item.title: Field - r744hhca
item.description: If set, coupling adapter ID and port number are valid Map: R744CHPA Based on: r744hfl1 Post-Processed This virtual field corresponds to the flag at bit-position 0 of field r744hfl1.

item.title: Field - r744hlat
item.description: Channel path latency time. Map: R744CHPA Based on: R744HLAT Description This is the average round-trip time in microseconds. A value of ‘0’ means that the time was not measured. A value of ‘1’ means a time less than or equal to one microsecond.

item.title: Field - r744hlav
item.description: If set, latency is valid Map: R744CHPA Based on: r744hfl1 Post-Processed This virtual field corresponds to the flag at bit-position 2 of field r744hfl1.

item.title: Field - r744hmov
item.description: If set, channel path operation mode is valid Map: R744CHPA Based on: r744hfl1 Post-Processed This virtual field corresponds to the flag at bit-position 1 of field r744hfl1.

item.title: Field - r744hopm
item.description: Channel path operation mode. Map: R744CHPA Based on: R744HOPM Description It describes the channel path type, data rate, protocol and adapter type. x'01’ - CFP path supporting a 1.0625 Gbit/sec data rate x'02’ - CFP path supporting a 2.125 Gbit/sec data rate x'10’ - CIB path operating at 1x bandwidth using the IFB protocol, adapter type HCA2-O LR x'11’ - CIB path operating at 12x bandwidth using the IFB protocol, adapter type HCA2-O x'20’ - CIB path operating at 1x bandwidth using the IFB protocol, adapter type HCA3-O LR x'21’ - CIB path operating at 12x bandwidth using the IFB protocol, adapter type HCA3-O x'30’ - CIB path operating at 12x bandwidth using the IFB3 protocol, adapter type HCA3-O x'40’ - CS5 path operating at 8x bandwidth using the GEN3 protocol, adapter type PCIe-O x'50’ - CL5 path supporting a 10 Gbit/sec data rate using the Converged Enhanced Ethernet protocol, adapter type RoCE LR

item.title: Field - r744hpcp
item.description: Physical channel path ID (CHID) Map: R744CHPA Based on: R744HPCP

item.title: Field - r744hpcv
item.description: If set, Channel ID (CHID) is valid Map: R744CHPA Based on: r744hfl2 Post-Processed This virtual field corresponds to the flag at bit-position 0 of field r744hfl2.

item.description: I/O processor to which this path is accessible. Map: R744CHPA Based on: R744HSAP Description The range of values is x'00’ to x’FF'.

item.title: Field - r744hsav

item.title: Field - r744mnel
item.description: The minimum number of list elements that must be available for assignment after the specified allocation process completes. Map: R744MSCM Based on: R744MNEL

item.title: Field - r744msrm

item.title: Field - r744mswc

item.title: Field - r744mwsq
item.description: Total amount of squares of service times for write operations to storage class memory in square-microseconds. Map: R744MSCM Based on: R744MWSQ

item.title: Field - r744mwst

item.title: Field - r744qrbn
item.description: New instance during rebuild Map: R744QSDS Based on: r744qflg Post-Processed This virtual field corresponds to the flag at bit-position 1 of field r744qflg.

item.title: Field - r744qrbo
item.description: Old instance during rebuild Map: R744QSDS Based on: r744qflg Post-Processed This virtual field corresponds to the flag at bit-position 2 of field r744qflg.

item.title: Field - r744qrbp
item.description: Structure rebuild in progress Map: R744QSDS Based on: r744qflg Post-Processed This virtual field corresponds to the flag at bit-position 6 of field r744qflg.

item.title: Field - r744qsiz

This count matches the number of subsequent channel path data sections associated with this remote CF.

item.title: Field - r7451gsf
item.description: Global Mirror Collisions (GMC) sidefile count (short float). Map: R7451DEV Based on: R7451GSF Description A GMC occurs when, during the sending of data in the secondary to create a consistency group, a subsequent host update is attempted before the modified track has been transmitted to the secondary volume. The modified track will be moved to the sidefile before allowing a new host write. The counter will be incremented by one when a track is added to the sidefile.

item.title: Field - r7451gss
item.description: Global Mirror Collisions Send synchronous count (short float). Map: R7451DEV Based on: R7451GSS Description When a write collision occurs, the modified track data which belongs to the current consistency group may be sent to the remote control unit before allowing the write. The data may come from the sidefile if it is full or from cache if the collision sidefile is not being utilized.

item.title: Field - r749rtrv

The range value of the remaining buckets represents response times less than this range value and greater than or equal to the prior range value.
